    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{1, 12, -17, -3, -11, -5\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean ($\\bar{x}$)\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1 + 12 + (-17) + (-3) + (-11) + (-5)}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{1 + 12 - 17 - 3 - 11 - 5}{6} = \\frac{-23}{6} \\approx -3.8333\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared deviations from the mean\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(1 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (4.8333)^2 \\approx 23.3704 \\\\\n(12 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (15.8333)^2 \\approx 250.734 \\\\\n(-17 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (-13.1667)^2 \\approx 173.370 \\\\\n(-3 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (0.8333)^2 \\approx 0.694 \\\\\n(-11 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (-7.1667)^2 \\approx 51.370 \\\\\n(-5 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (-1.1667)^2 \\approx 1.361 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared deviations\n\n$$\n\\sum (x_i - \\bar{x})^2 \\approx 23.3704 + 250.734 + 173.370 + 0.694 + 51.370 + 1.361 \\approx 500.399\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $n - 1$ (sample variance formula)\n\n$$\ns^2 = \\frac{500.399}{6 - 1} = \\frac{500.399}{5}"
}